Missions.Title: First escape
Missions.Description: Get out of the bio wing. But be careful, they already sent "problem solvers" to deal with you.

Missions.Title: Restricted area
Missions.Description: You are looking for clues, but it seems you have to look in another facility. To get there, you must trespass a restricted area, with the special unit still on your tail.

Objectives.Description: Blow up that warhead as distration.

Missions.Title: The archives
Missions.Description: You break into the archives, looking for more information about yourself. Watch out, there are guards everywhere!

Objectives.Description: Get rid of the containment special force.

Missions.Title: Classified information
Missions.Description: You read the documents. It turns out you are one of many experiments in this base. Other projects are "The Fallen", "Project Nexus", "Project Brutus" and "The Specters". You decide to check this out and leave the archives through the service tunnels.

Objectives.Description: Looks like some experiments already killed someone.
Nice poster that looks like a map.

Missions.Title: Weaponry research test facility
Missions.Description: To get to "The Fallen" you have to cross the weapon research facility. Be careful, silent alarm has been activated since you left your lab.

Missions.Title: The Fallen
Missions.Description: As you meet "The Fallen" you notice: Those are braindead, zombie-like creatures. There is nothing you can do for them. You decide to pit them against your followers by creating a diversion.

Missions.Title: Cyberwarfare labs
Missions.Description: Your distraction more or less worked. To get to "Project Brutus" you need to pass the cyberwarfare wing, a giant data center.

Objectives.Description: I wonder what this will get on CyberBay...
What a fine brand of liqueur.

Missions.Title: Project Brutus
Missions.Description: As you enter the room, you get attacked by the project, an attempt to create a neurologically linked cyborg.

Missions.Title: Heavy armory
Missions.Description: To get to project Nexus and "The Specters" you need to pass the heavy armory. You might want to be careful there.

Objectives.Description: I wonder who left this here...

Missions.Title: Nexus
Missions.Description: There is no sign of a "Specter". One scientist says the last one alive fled from the death squads. However, Nexus is still here and you better rescue it.

Missions.Title: Run for it
Missions.Description: Chaos is everywhere. You decide to use that opportunity to get to the heliport. Apparently you know how to fly such a thing. How convenient!

Objectives.Description: Would be a dick move to take her stuff but let her to die...

Missions.Title: The last specter
Missions.Description: As you are about to enter the heli, you hear the SHHK-SHHK of a shotgun. "So you and your friendos want to use the chopter? It's you or me, bucko!" So be it.

Objectives.Description: Kill the "Specter" so you all can enter the chopper!
